\pard\f0\fs28 Stems short or elongated. Leaves submerged, alternate, sessile, linear. Flowers usually hermaphrodite. Spathes tubular, axillary, sessile, 1-flowered. Petals linear, longer than the sepals. Stamens 3. Ovary sessile within the spathe, attenuated into a long, filiform beak, styles 3, simple, linear, connate at the base.
