\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. B. japonica} (Miq.) Maxim. in Engler & Prantl, Natürl. Pflanzenfam. 2(1): 253 (1889). Stems elongated. Leaves up to 70 × 3·5 mm, minutely denticulate. Spathes sessile. Sepals 3-4 mm. Petals 6-10 mm, white.{\i  Naturalized in rice-fields in N. Italy and S.W. Portugal}. [It Lu.] ({\i S.E. Asia.})
